            "ratingValue": "3",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I’ve had my son enrolled at Podar School, Indore, for the past four years. His academic progress has been excellent, and we’ve always been satisfied with the teaching quality. However, I’m extremely disappointed with the school administration's support lately, particularly regarding the transportation services.\n\nThe school bus no longer picks up my son from our home or a nearby location. Instead, we’ve been told he must go to a designated stop set by the administration, which is quite inconvenient. The lack of flexibility and support from the admin team has made this situation very frustrating for us. I sincerely hope they reconsider their transportation policy to better accommodate the students and families.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
